From 2da6725dad1ebcd93f437b0bd469655ee1452c66 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: M4 Patch Rebase <claude-rebase@m4.local>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 22:42:08 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Patches 013+016-020: VLM pixel_values + multimodal extras +
 NemotronH/Gemma 4 sliding-window

Combined commit for the 6 patches whose v0.5.11-base versions either had
malformed hunk headers (013, 017, 018) or order dependencies on 013 (016)
that prevented clean sequential application against v0.5.12. The patches:

- 013: VLM pixel_values + mm_kwargs plumbing in prefill/prefill_start +
       tp_worker.py forwarding from req.multimodal_inputs
- 016: bf16->float32 numpy bridge in tp_worker.py
- 017: nemotron-omni video alignment (nano_nemotron_vl.py)
- 018: gemma4 unpatch (siglip2 reverse in tp_worker.py)
- 019: NemotronH partial-cache serial fallback in decode_batch_start
- 020: gemma4 RotatingKVCache update_and_fetch + sliding-window fallback

These all live in 4 files (model_runner.py, tp_worker.py,
attention_wrapper.py, nano_nemotron_vl.py) and are conceptually
related (multimodal + heterogeneous-attention support). The other
13 patches (002-012, 014, 015) are now per-feature commits.
